    <h1>Mental health</h1>
    <p>
        Mental health is critically important for individuals dealing with chronic diseases for several reasons:
    </p>
    <div class="content">
        <h2>1. Quality of Life </h2>
        <p>Chronic diseases often come with various symptoms and limitations, affecting a person's overall quality of life.<br />Mental health support can help individuals cope with these challenges, leading to a better quality of life despite the chronic condition</p>
        <h3>2. Emotional Well-being </h3>
        <p>Managing a chronic disease can lead to feelings of stress, anxiety, and depression. <br />Mental health support provides tools to cope with these emotions, promoting emotional well-being and resilience.</p>
        <h4>3.Treatment Adherence</h4>
        <p>Mental health issues can impact a person's ability to adhere to their treatment plans. Depression or anxiety, for example, might lead to neglecting medications or avoiding necessary lifestyle changes.<br /> Addressing mental health concerns can improve treatment adherence.</p>
        <h5>4.Pain Management</h5>
        <p>Chronic diseases often involve pain. Mental health techniques, such as cognitive behavioral therapy, <br />can help individuals manage pain perception and improve their ability to cope with discomfort</p>
